# Intendfile — Design intent declarations for lustreiser
# Author: Jonathan D.A. Jewell <j.d.a.jewell@open.ac.uk>

@abstract:
What lustreiser INTENDS to become. These are bespoke design goals
specific to the Safety-critical real-time embedded systems domain.
@end

## Domain-Specific Intent

### real-time-certification\n- description: Enable DO-178C/IEC-61508 certification for generated code\n- target: Traceable requirements, MC/DC coverage, formal WCET proofs\n- status: aspiration\n\n### multi-target-codegen\n- description: Generate code for ARM Cortex-M, RISC-V, and x86 targets\n- target: Platform-specific timing models\n- status: aspiration

## Cross-Cutting Intent

### iser-ecosystem-compatibility
- description: Must interoperate with other -iser projects via shared ABI
- target: Idris2 ABI + Zig FFI standard interface
- status: in-progress

### proven-integration
- description: All formal proofs should be verifiable by the proven framework
- target: Integration with hyperpolymath/proven
- status: aspiration
